-- Persian Gulf Stocks: Etisalat in Abu Dhabi and Vodafone Qatar
-- B y   Z a h r a   H a n k i r
-- 2012-06-07T10:51:16Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-07/persian-gulf-stocks-etisalat-in-abu-dhabi-and-vodafone-qatar.html
Dubai’s benchmark  DFM General Index (DFMGI) 
gained for a third day, rising 0.5 percent to 1,463.69 at the 2
p.m. close in the emirate. The index lost 0.5 percent this week.
Qatar’s  QE Index (DSM)  declined 0.3 percent.  The following shares were active in the Persian Gulf
region. Stock symbols are in parentheses.  Emirates Telecommunications Corp. (ETISALAT)  , the phone
company known as Etisalat, advanced the most since May 14,
increasing 0.3 percent to 8.82 dirhams. A law that governs
Etisalat may be amended to allow foreigner investors to own
shares, Emarat Alyoum said on its website, citing people it
didn’t identify.  Vodafone Qatar (VFQS)   climbed 1.4 percent, the most
since May 23, to 9.24 riyals. The venture between Vodafone Group
LLC and state-controlled  Qatar Foundation  may announce fourth-
quarter results today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Zahra Hankir in Dubai at 
 zhankir@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
